Dynamic Memory Alocation : way to allocate memory to data structure during runtime

Fucntions: 

mallooc() : memory allocation 
Takes number of bytes to be allocated & returns a pointer of type void
--> ptr  (int*)malloc(5*sizeof(int));
                   "sizeof:  function = return size"
                   sizeof(int) = 4 bytes
                   if 5 elememnts: sizeof(array)=20
                   
int* : typecast to integer 
otherwise it is void pointer

calloc(): continous allocation
initialize with 0 == store null value (zero)
every value zero
ptr = (int*)calloc(5,sizeof(int));

free() : free memory allocated using malloc&calloc
free(ptr);

realloc() : increase or decrease memory i=using same poinntter and size

ptr = realloc(ptr,newsize);

